.TH PHASORRT\-ZIG 3 "May 2026" "phasorrt" "Phasor Runtime Library 3.3.0"
.SH NAME
phasorrt\-zig \- Zig wrapper for the Phasor Runtime
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B const phasorrt = @import("phasorrt");
.PP
.B pub const PhasorError = error{ ... };
.PP
.B phasorrt.getVersion()
.B phasorrt.compilePHS(allocator, script, module_name, module_path)
.B phasorrt.compilePUL(allocator, script, module_name)
.PP
.B State.create()
.B State.deinit(self)
.B State.reset(self, reset_functions, reset_variables)
.B State.exec(self, bytecode, module_name, args)
.B State.execFuncInt(self, bytecode, module_name, args, function_name)
.B State.execFuncString(self, bytecode, module_name, args, function_name)
.B State.evaluatePHS(self, script, module_name, module_path, verbose)
.B State.evaluatePUL(self, script, module_name)
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The Zig wrapper provides idiomatic Zig bindings for the Phasor Runtime dynamic
library. The native library is loaded once on first use via
.B std.once
and is kept open for the lifetime of the process. All public functions return
.B PhasorError
as the error set of an error union, eliminating the need to inspect raw
.B \-1
or
.B NULL
sentinel values.
.PP
VM state is encapsulated in the
.B State
struct.
.B State.create()
both allocates the native state and registers the standard library in a
single call, so
.B initStdLib
need not be invoked separately.
.B State.deinit()
releases the native state and should be paired with every successful call
to
.B State.create()
(a
.B defer
is idiomatic).
.PP
The compilation functions,
.B compilePHS()
and
.BR compilePUL() ,
are free functions that accept an
.B std.mem.Allocator
and return a caller-owned
.B []u8
slice. The caller is responsible for freeing the slice with the same
allocator.
.SH TYPES
.TP
.B PhasorError
The error set shared by all public functions:
.RS
.IP \fBLibraryNotFound\fR 22
The native library could not be opened.
.IP \fBSymbolNotFound\fR 22
One or more required symbols were absent from the library.
.IP \fBStateCreationFailed\fR 22
The native
.B createState()
call returned a null pointer.
.IP \fBVmException\fR 22
The VM raised an unhandled exception (native return code
.BR \-1 ).
.IP \fBNullStringReturn\fR 22
A function expected to return a string pointer returned null.
.IP \fBCompilationFailed\fR 22
The Phasor compiler rejected the source text.
.IP \fBStateFailed\fR 22
A state-management operation (e.g.\&
.BR reset )
returned false from the native library.
.IP \fBOutOfMemory\fR 22
The allocator could not satisfy an allocation request.
.RE
.TP
.B State
An opaque handle to a Phasor VM instance. Contains a single field,
.BR ptr ,
which holds the native state pointer. Do not access
.B ptr
directly.
.SH FUNCTIONS
.SS Free Functions
.TP
.BR getVersion ()
Return the version string of the loaded Phasor Runtime library.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
None
.PP
.B Returns:
.B PhasorError![]const u8
\(em a slice pointing into a static buffer managed by the runtime.
The caller must not free or mutate this slice.
.RE
.TP
.BR compilePHS (allocator,\ script,\ module_name,\ module_path)
Compile a Phasor (PHS) source string to bytecode. Uses a two-pass strategy:
the first pass determines the required buffer size; the second fills it.
The returned slice is caller-owned.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
.RS
.IP \fBallocator\fR 16
.B std.mem.Allocator
used for the bytecode buffer. The caller must free
the returned slice with the same allocator when done.
.IP \fBscript\fR 16
Null-terminated PHS source text
.RB ( [:0]const\ u8 ).
.IP \fBmodule_name\fR 16
Null-terminated module name used in error messages
.RB ( [:0]const\ u8 ).
.IP \fBmodule_path\fR 16
Null-terminated filesystem path to the script's parent directory for
resolving imports
.RB ( [:0]const\ u8 ).
Pass
.B ""
if imports are not needed.
.RE
.PP
.B Returns:
.B PhasorError![]u8
\(em caller-owned bytecode buffer suitable for passing to
.BR State.exec() .
Returns
.B PhasorError.CompilationFailed
if the compiler rejects the source, or
.B PhasorError.OutOfMemory
if allocation fails.
.RE
.TP
.BR compilePUL (allocator,\ script,\ module_name)
Compile a Pulsar (PUL) source string to bytecode. Behaves identically to
.B compilePHS()
except that no
.I module_path
is required.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
.RS
.IP \fBallocator\fR 16
See
.BR compilePHS() .
.IP \fBscript\fR 16
Null-terminated PUL source text
.RB ( [:0]const\ u8 ).
.IP \fBmodule_name\fR 16
Null-terminated module name used in error messages
.RB ( [:0]const\ u8 ).
.RE
.PP
.B Returns:
.B PhasorError![]u8
\(em same semantics as
.BR compilePHS() .
.RE
.SS State Methods
.TP
.BR State.create ()
Allocate a new VM state and register the Phasor standard library. This
combines the native
.B createState()
and
.B initStdLib()
calls into one operation.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
None
.PP
.B Returns:
.B PhasorError!State
\(em a fully initialised
.B State
value, or
.B PhasorError.StateCreationFailed
if the native allocation fails.
.RE
.TP
.BR State.deinit (self)
Release the native VM state. After
.B deinit()
returns the
.B State
value must not be used again. Errors from the underlying
.B freeState()
call are silently discarded.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
.RS
.IP \fBself\fR 8
A valid
.B State
value previously returned by
.BR State.create() .
.RE
.PP
.B Returns:
.B void
.RE
.TP
.BR State.reset (self,\ reset_functions,\ reset_variables)
Reset VM internals: clear the execution stack, reset the program counter,
and unload any loaded bytecode. Registered functions and global variables
are cleared only when the corresponding flag is set.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
.RS
.IP \fBself\fR 20
A valid
.B State
value.
.IP \fBreset_functions\fR 20
If
.BR true ,
all user-registered functions are unregistered.
.IP \fBreset_variables\fR 20
If
.BR true ,
all global variables are cleared.
.RE
.PP
.B Returns:
.B PhasorError!void
\(em returns
.B PhasorError.StateFailed
if the native call indicates failure.
.RE
.TP
.BR State.exec (self,\ bytecode,\ module_name,\ args)
Load bytecode into the VM and execute it.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
.RS
.IP \fBself\fR 16
A valid
.B State
value.
.IP \fBbytecode\fR 16
Compiled bytecode slice
.RB ( []const\ u8 )
produced by
.B compilePHS()
or
.BR compilePUL() .
.IP \fBmodule_name\fR 16
Null-terminated module name for error reporting
.RB ( [:0]const\ u8 ).
.IP \fBargs\fR 16
Slice of null-terminated argument strings
.RB ( []const\ [*:0]const\ u8 ).
The first element (index 0) is conventionally the program name. Pass
.B &.{}
for an empty argument list.
.RE
.PP
.B Returns:
.B PhasorError!i32
\(em the integer exit code returned by the script. Returns
.B PhasorError.VmException
if the VM raises an unhandled exception.
.RE
.TP
.BR State.execFuncInt (self,\ bytecode,\ module_name,\ args,\ function_name)
Load bytecode and call a specific exported function, expecting an integer
return value.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
As for
.BR State.exec() ,
with the addition of:
.RS
.IP \fBfunction_name\fR 16
Null-terminated name of the exported function to invoke
.RB ( [:0]const\ u8 ).
.RE
.PP
.B Returns:
.B PhasorError!i32
\(em the integer value returned by the function, or
.B PhasorError.VmException
on error.
.RE
.TP
.BR State.execFuncString (self,\ bytecode,\ module_name,\ args,\ function_name)
Load bytecode and call a specific exported function, expecting a string
return value.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
As for
.BR State.execFuncInt() .
.PP
.B Returns:
.B PhasorError![:0]const\\ u8
\(em a null-terminated slice pointing into memory owned by the Phasor runtime.
This slice is invalidated on the next call to
.B execFuncString()
and when
.B deinit()
is called. Copy the contents to safe storage if the string must outlive
either of those events.
Returns
.B PhasorError.NullStringReturn
if the function returns a null pointer, or
.B PhasorError.VmException
on an unhandled exception.
.RE
.TP
.BR State.evaluatePHS (self,\ script,\ module_name,\ module_path,\ verbose)
Compile and immediately execute a Phasor (PHS) source string in one step.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
.RS
.IP \fBself\fR 16
A valid
.B State
value.
.IP \fBscript\fR 16
Null-terminated PHS source text
.RB ( [:0]const\ u8 ).
.IP \fBmodule_name\fR 16
Null-terminated module name for error reporting
.RB ( [:0]const\ u8 ).
.IP \fBmodule_path\fR 16
Null-terminated path to the script's parent directory for resolving imports
.RB ( [:0]const\ u8 ).
Pass
.B ""
if unused.
.IP \fBverbose\fR 16
If
.BR true ,
the abstract syntax tree is printed to standard output.
.RE
.PP
.B Returns:
.B PhasorError!i32
\(em script exit code, or
.B PhasorError.VmException
on an unhandled exception.
.RE
.TP
.BR State.evaluatePUL (self,\ script,\ module_name)
Compile and immediately execute a Pulsar (PUL) source string in one step.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
.RS
.IP \fBself\fR 16
A valid
.B State
value.
.IP \fBscript\fR 16
Null-terminated PUL source text
.RB ( [:0]const\ u8 ).
.IP \fBmodule_name\fR 16
Null-terminated module name for error reporting
.RB ( [:0]const\ u8 ).
.RE
.PP
.B Returns:
.B PhasorError!i32
\(em script exit code, or
.B PhasorError.VmException
on an unhandled exception.
.RE
.SH ERRORS
All public functions return
.B PhasorError
as their error set. The error values and the functions that produce them
are:
.TP
.B PhasorError.LibraryNotFound
Returned by any function on first use if
.B std.DynLib.open()
fails to locate the native library. The library name is platform-specific:
.B phasorrt.dll
on Windows,
.B libphasorrt.dylib
on macOS, and
.B libphasorrt.so
elsewhere.
.TP
.B PhasorError.SymbolNotFound
The native library was found but one or more required symbols were absent.
Indicates a version mismatch between the wrapper and the installed runtime.
.TP
.B PhasorError.StateCreationFailed
Returned by
.B State.create()
when the native
.B createState()
returns a null pointer.
.TP
.B PhasorError.CompilationFailed
Returned by
.BR compilePHS() ,
.BR compilePUL() ,
and the
.B evaluate
family when the Phasor compiler rejects the source. Diagnostic output may
be written to
.B stderr
by the runtime.
.TP
.B PhasorError.VmException
Returned by
.BR State.exec() ,
.BR State.execFuncInt() ,
.BR State.execFuncString() ,
.BR State.evaluatePHS() ,
and
.B State.evaluatePUL()
when the VM raises an unhandled exception (native return code
.BR \-1 ).
.TP
.B PhasorError.NullStringReturn
Returned by
.B State.execFuncString()
when the invoked function returns a null string pointer.
.TP
.B PhasorError.StateFailed
Returned by
.B State.reset()
when the native
.B resetState()
call returns false.
.TP
.B PhasorError.OutOfMemory
Returned by
.B compilePHS()
and
.B compilePUL()
when the provided allocator cannot satisfy a buffer allocation.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic script evaluation
.nf
.RS
const phasorrt = @import("phasorrt");
const std = @import("std");

pub fn main() !void {
    const version = try phasorrt.getVersion();
    std.debug.print("Runtime version: {s}\\n", .{version});

    const vm = try phasorrt.State.create();
    defer vm.deinit();

    _ = try vm.evaluatePHS(
        "print(\\"Hello from Zig!\\\\n\\");",
        "main",
        "",
        false,
    );
}
.RE
.fi
.SS Compile then execute
.nf
.RS
const phasorrt = @import("phasorrt");
const std = @import("std");

pub fn main() !void {
    var gpa = std.heap.GeneralPurposeAllocator(.{}){};
    defer _ = gpa.deinit();
    const alloc = gpa.allocator();

    const bytecode = try phasorrt.compilePHS(
        alloc,
        "var x = 42; print(x);",
        "main",
        "",
    );
    defer alloc.free(bytecode);

    const vm = try phasorrt.State.create();
    defer vm.deinit();

    const code = try vm.exec(bytecode, "main", &.{});
    std.debug.print("Exit code: {}\\n", .{code});
}
.RE
.fi
.SS Calling an exported function
.nf
.RS
const phasorrt = @import("phasorrt");
const std = @import("std");

pub fn main() !void {
    var gpa = std.heap.GeneralPurposeAllocator(.{}){};
    defer _ = gpa.deinit();
    const alloc = gpa.allocator();

    const src = "fn greet() { return \\"hello from phasor\\"; }";
    const bytecode = try phasorrt.compilePHS(alloc, src, "greet", "");
    defer alloc.free(bytecode);

    const vm = try phasorrt.State.create();
    defer vm.deinit();

    /* returned slice is runtime-owned; copy before the next call */
    const result = try vm.execFuncString(bytecode, "greet", &.{}, "greet");
    const owned = try alloc.dupe(u8, result);
    defer alloc.free(owned);

    std.debug.print("{s}\\n", .{owned});
}
.RE
.fi
.SS Resetting VM state between runs
.nf
.RS
try vm.evaluatePHS(script_a, "a", "", false);
try vm.reset(false, true);   /* clear variables, keep functions */
try vm.evaluatePHS(script_b, "b", "", false);
.RE
.fi
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
The native library is loaded once, on the first call to any public function,
using
.BR std.once .
All subsequent calls reuse the already-resolved symbol table. If the initial
load fails,
.B PhasorError.LibraryNotFound
or
.B PhasorError.SymbolNotFound
is returned on every subsequent call without retrying.
.IP \(bu 2
.B State
is not thread-safe. Do not share a single
.B State
value across threads without external synchronisation. Create one
.B State
per thread for concurrent use.
.IP \(bu 2
The slice returned by
.B State.execFuncString()
is owned by the Phasor runtime and is overwritten on the next call to
that function. Always copy the contents before calling
.B execFuncString()
again or before calling
.BR deinit() .
.IP \(bu 2
.B compilePHS()
and
.B compilePUL()
return a caller-owned
.B []u8
slice that must be freed with the same allocator that was passed in.
Failure to free the slice is a memory leak.
.IP \(bu 2
.B State.create()
registers the standard library automatically. Calling
.B initStdLib
manually through the native C API on the same state is not needed and
may produce unexpected behaviour.
